  "text": "This approach significantly reduces the confounding influence of any peptides whose precursor ion signal overlaps with the analytes of interest. Because of the complexity of biological samples, it is important to validate the quantification calculated using the precursor ion population alone if using limited or no peptide/ protein separation pre-MS. In our work, two independently selected isotopic variants (arising from labeled QconCAT and native chicken protein) constitute a precursor ion population that is subsequently fragmented by IRMPD [CITATION_1] . We have demonstrated the utility of this approach for absolute quantification of proteins within unfractionated chicken muscle protein.",
